name: invertemple
description: This is a digital art piece I created on 01/08/2006 at 19:08 using an old school program called Roxio Photosuite as part of my 'Flashcore x photography' collection. Something I made when I was 15 years old as an aspiring artist and photographer, but never published. I just created for fun. I’m now 30 and am finally sharing this piece and many more I’ve found from my old CD and USB drives. This is a photo I took of St. Matthew's Church in Walsall, UK. A beautiful grade II* listed building built around 1220 with some parts re-built in 1820. I then edited it in Photosuite to create a grungy inverted glitch style. As I was an emo scene teen! :)
